%description:
Stateful address configuration via DHCPv6. [RFC 8415; NOT-MODELED]

Where stateless autoconfiguration is not used (e.g. a Router Advertisement with the Managed-address
flag set, or no autonomous prefix), a host obtains its address from a DHCPv6 server, beginning with
a SOLICIT to the All-DHCP-Relay-Agents-and-Servers multicast on UDP port 547. INET has no DHCPv6
client -- there is no DHCPv6 message set or module at all -- so no host ever sends a SOLICIT; the
faithful spec assertion times out (an expected failure: DHCPv6 is not modeled).

%file: Dhcpv6_Solicit.cc

#include "ProtocolTest.h"

namespace inet {
namespace protocoltest {

Define_ProtocolTest(ipv6_dhcpv6_solicit)
{
    return ProtocolTest("ipv6_dhcpv6_solicit")
        .once(on("host1.eth[0].mac").signal("packetSentToLower")
                  .packet("udp.destPort == 547")
                  .describe("a DHCPv6 SOLICIT from host1").within(8.0));
}

} // namespace protocoltest
} // namespace inet

%inifile: test.ini

[General]
*.tester.testName = "ipv6_dhcpv6_solicit"
include ../../ini/_base.ini

%contains: stdout
PROTOCOLTEST ipv6_dhcpv6_solicit: FAIL
